6. A moving mathematical object

A static object might be represented as:

triangle = {
    "a": 3,
    "b": 4,
    "c": 5,
}

A moving object includes:

* state,
* transformation,
* history,
* constraints,
* possible futures.

@dataclass
class DynamicObject:
    state: State
    history: list[State]
    def evolve(
        self,
        environment: Environment,
        parameters: Parameters,
        dt: float,
    ) -> None:
        self.history.append(self.state)
        delta = compute_delta(
            self.state,
            environment,
            parameters,
            dt,
        )
        self.state = apply_delta(self.state, delta)

The object is no longer merely its current values.

It is:

\text{Object}
=
\text{current state}
+
\text{history}
+
\text{transition rules}
+
\text{reachable futures}

That is much closer to identity in a changing system.

